2.20	Zoroashtrianism	Zoroastrianism	Zoroastrianism (or Mazdaism) is a religion and philosophy based on the teachings of prophet Zoroaster (also known as Zarathustra, in Avestan) and was formerly among the world's largest religions. It was probably founded some time before the 6th century BCE in Greater Iran.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Faravahar-Gold.svg/140px-Faravahar-Gold.svg.png
